-- EU Leaders Discuss G-20 Summit on Video Call, Officials Say
-- B y   T o n y   C z u c z k a   a n d   E d d i e   B u c k l e
-- 2012-06-15T18:16:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-15/eu-leaders-complete-call-before-g-20-summit-german-aide-says.html
European leaders held a video
conference call to discuss the Group of 20 talks, German and
British officials said.  The call was to address the G-20 agenda including the
global economy and the crisis in the euro area, U.K. Prime
Minister  David Cameron ’s spokesman Steve Field said earlier
today.  Participants included Cameron, Germany’s Angela Merkel,
France’s Francois Hollande, Mario Monti of Italy, Spain’s
Mariano Rajoy and  Herman Van Rompuy  and  Jose Barroso  of the
European Union. The summit begins June 18 in Los Cabos, Mexico.  The EU’s priorities for the G-20 summit include ensuring
global coordination to promote sustainable, balanced economic
growth and implementation of the group’s commitments on
financial-market reform, Cameron’s office said in an e-mailed
statement.  To contact the reporters on this story:
